00748 void AnaFillResult::CalcBeamPolar(Bool_t doNorm)
00749 {
00750    PolarimeterIdSetIter iPolId = gRunConfig.fPolarimeters.begin();
00751 
00752    for ( ; iPolId != gRunConfig.fPolarimeters.end(); ++iPolId)
00753    {
00754       EPolarimeterId polId        = *iPolId;
00755       ValErrPair     pcPolar      = GetPCPolar(polId);
00756       ValErrPair     pcPolarP0    = GetPCPolarP0(polId);
00757       ValErrPair     pcPolarDecay = GetPCPolarSlope(polId);
00758       ERingId        ringId       = RunConfig::GetRingId(polId);
00759 
00760       if (!fAnaGlobResult)
00761          Warning("CalcBeamPolar", "fAnaGlobResult not defined in fill %d", fFillId);
00762 
00763       Double_t norm = doNorm && fAnaGlobResult ? fAnaGlobResult->GetNormJetCarbon(polId).first : 1;
00764 
00765       if (pcPolar.second >= 0)      { pcPolar.first      *= norm;  pcPolar.second      *= norm; }
00766       if (pcPolarP0.second >= 0)    { pcPolarP0.first    *= norm;  pcPolarP0.second    *= norm; }
00767       if (pcPolarDecay.second >= 0) { pcPolarDecay.first *= norm;  pcPolarDecay.second *= norm; }
00768 
00769       if ( fBeamPolars.find(ringId) == fBeamPolars.end() ) {
00770          fBeamPolars[ringId]      = pcPolar;
00771          fBeamPolarP0s[ringId]    = pcPolarP0;
00772          fBeamPolarSlopes[ringId] = pcPolarDecay;
00773       } else {
00774          fBeamPolars[ringId]      = utils::CalcWeightedAvrgErr(fBeamPolars[ringId],      pcPolar);
00775          fBeamPolarP0s[ringId]    = utils::CalcWeightedAvrgErr(fBeamPolarP0s[ringId],    pcPolarP0);
00776          fBeamPolarSlopes[ringId] = utils::CalcWeightedAvrgErr(fBeamPolarSlopes[ringId], pcPolarDecay);
00777       }
00778    }
00779 }

00969 ValErrPair AnaFillResult::CalcAvrgPolar(EPolarimeterId polId)
00970 {
00971    ValErrPair avrgPol(0, -1);
00972 
00973    // Check that we have graph
00974    const TGraphErrors *grPCPolar = GetPCPolarGraph(polId);
00975    if (!grPCPolar) {
00976       Warning("CalcAvrgPolar", "Fill %d. No graph defined for polId %d", fFillId, polId);
00977       return avrgPol;
00978    } else {
00979       Warning("CalcAvrgPolar", "Fill %d. Graph defined for polId %d", fFillId, polId);
00980    }
00981 
00982    // Check that graph has fit func
00983    TF1* funcPCPolar = grPCPolar->GetFunction("fitFunc");
00984    if (!funcPCPolar) {
00985       Warning("CalcAvrgPolar", "Fill %d. No fit function found in graph for polId %d", fFillId, polId);
00986       return avrgPol;
00987    }
00988 
00989    // Get intens graph
00990    ERingId ringId = RunConfig::GetRingId(polId);
00991 
00992    TGraphErrors *grIntens = GetIntensGraph(ringId);
00993    if (!grIntens) {
00994       Warning("CalcAvrgPolar", "No intensity graph available for weighted average calculation %d. Unweighted average returned", polId);
00995       avrgPol = CalcAvrgPolarUnweighted(polId);
00996       return avrgPol;
00997    }
00998 
00999    Double_t time, intens, polar, polarErr;
01000    Double_t numer = 0, denom = 0, numerErr = 0, denomErr = 0;
01001 
01002    Double_t polarNormErr  = funcPCPolar->GetParError(0);
01003    Double_t polarSlopeErr = funcPCPolar->GetParError(1);
01004 
01005    for (UInt_t iPoint=0; iPoint < (UInt_t) grIntens->GetN(); iPoint++)
01006    {
01007       grIntens->GetPoint(iPoint, time, intens);
01008       polar = funcPCPolar->Eval(time);
01009 
01010       numer += polar*intens;
01011       denom += intens;
01012 
01013       // assume no correlation between the polarization slope (par1) and norm (par0)
01014       polarErr = sqrt( polarSlopeErr*polarSlopeErr*(time - GetLumiOnRelTime())*(time - GetLumiOnRelTime())/3600/3600 + polarNormErr*polarNormErr);
01015       numerErr += polarErr*intens;
01016       denomErr += intens;
01017    }
01018 
01019    // Internaly all polarization values are between 0 and 1 except graphs
01020    avrgPol.first  = numer/denom/100.;
01021    avrgPol.second = numerErr/denomErr/100.; // weighted error
01022 
01023    return avrgPol;
01024 }

01208 ValErrPair AnaFillResult::CalcPolProfP(ValErrPair R, ValErrPair PMax)
01209 {
01210    ValErrPair polProfP(0, -1);
01211 
01212    if (PMax.second < 0 || R.second < 0 || R.first <= -1) return polProfP;
01213 
01214    polProfP.first = PMax.first / sqrt(1 + R.first);
01215 
01216    Double_t delta2 = PMax.first * PMax.first * R.second *
01217                      R.second/4./(1+R.first)/(1+R.first)/(1+R.first) +
01218                      PMax.second * PMax.second / (1 + R.first);
01219 
01220    polProfP.second = sqrt(delta2);
01221 
01222    return polProfP;

01434 void AnaFillResult::FitPCPolarGraphs()
01435 {
01436    // Fit the polarization decay graphs
01437    // Create a function to multiply graphs by 100% for aesthetic reasons
01438    TF2 *dummyScale = new TF2("dummyScale", "100.*y");
01439 
01440    PolarimeterIdSetIter iPolId = gRunConfig.fPolarimeters.begin();
01441    for ( ; iPolId != gRunConfig.fPolarimeters.end(); ++iPolId)
01442    {
01443       EPolarimeterId polId = *iPolId;
01444 
01445       // Fit injection measurements first...
01446       TGraphErrors *grPCPolarInj = GetPCPolarInjGraph(polId);
01447 
01448       // All of this has to be combined with FT measurements and processed the same way
01449       if (grPCPolarInj)
01450       {
01451          grPCPolarInj->Apply(dummyScale);
01452 
01453          if (grPCPolarInj->GetN() >= 2)
01454          {
01455             Double_t xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax;
01456             grPCPolarInj->ComputeRange(xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax);
01457

01459             {
01460                Info("FitPCPolarGraphs", "Fill %d. Fitting injection graph for polId %d", fFillId, polId);
01461 
01462                TF1 *fitFunc = new TF1("fitFunc", "pol0");
01463                fitFunc->SetParNames("P_{0}, %");
01464                grPCPolarInj->Fit(fitFunc, "", "", xmin, xmax);
01465 
01466                delete fitFunc;
01467             }
01468          }
01469       }
01470 
01471       // Fit flattop measurements...
01472       TGraphErrors *grPCPolar  = GetPCPolarGraph(polId);
01473 
01474       if (!grPCPolar || grPCPolar->GetN() <= 0) continue; // require a valid graph
01475 
01476       grPCPolar->Apply(dummyScale);
01477 
01478       stringstream ssFormula("");
01479       ssFormula << "[0] + [1]*(x - (" << GetLumiOnRelTime() << ") )/3600.";
01480 
01481       TF1 *fitFunc = new TF1("fitFunc", ssFormula.str().c_str());
01482       fitFunc->SetParNames("P_{0}, %", "Decay, %/h");

01489          TGraph *tmpGraph = utils::SubGraph(grPCPolar, GetLumiOnRelTime(), GetLumiOffRelTime());
01490 
01491          if (tmpGraph->GetN() >= 1) {
01492             tmpGraph->ComputeRange(xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax);
01493 
01494             if (fabs(xmax - xmin) < 3600)
01495                fitFunc->FixParameter(1, 0);
01496 
01497             xmin = GetLumiOnRelTime();
01498             xmax = GetLumiOffRelTime();
01499          } else { // go back to original limits
01500             if (fabs(xmax - xmin) < 3600)
01501                fitFunc->FixParameter(1, 0);
01502          }
01503 
01504          delete tmpGraph;
01505       } else {
01506 
01507          if (fabs(xmax - xmin) < 3600)
01508             fitFunc->FixParameter(1, 0);
01509       }
01510 
01511       // fit with a const if only one data point is available
